node.text:
Why perform drop sets? ⤵️

Drop sets are a fantastic way to increase the intensity and potential muscle growth during your sessions, it’s a very effective way to cause huge muscular and metabolic stress, and these stresses are great for hypertrophy. 

The goal when performing dropsets, is to push your muscles past the point where you would normally succumb to the build up of latic acid, so essentially by reducing the weight and continuing on with the set, you are fatiguing the muscles completely. 

⚠️ As you work through dropsets it can become difficult to maintain proper form, there is always a window for small decline with form when dropsetting, but do ensure your lifts are safe. 

👉You can download my training programs at simeonpanda.com

#simeonpanda #chanelcocobrown #dropset #seatedrow

node.text:
Tag and share this with as many people as possible🔥 It’s important to understand that when it comes to ‘revealing’ your abs (we all have them, only difference is their prominence) the fat burning portion of your workouts and what you consume on a daily basis, will have far more significance in helping you achieve that goal than all the abs work you do. 

Now I used the term ‘revealing’ as it is a goal sort by many which is separate to building, just wanting to see those lines come through, is not the same as wanting to ‘build’ your abs. Clearly to build the abdominal muscles you need to train them, but there is a huge misconception that just training them in isolation, will miraculously emulsify the fat that hides them, it won’t.

This is why I always encourage those seeking abs to be mindful of their body fat, evaluate your starting position, you may decide that your time could be better spent on exercises that torch more calories and lower your body fat, than doing a 1000 crunches.

👉 You can watch this video in full on my YouTube channel, search: How to get 6 pack abs [The Facts]

👉 You can download my Six Pack Extreme Training Guide where I explain all of this in detail, provide complete workouts and advice on nutrition to get you those abs quicker! Visit SIMEONPANDA.COM | Link in bio

👉 Add @innosupps Innoshred & Volcarn 2000 to your daily supps to turn up the heat 🔥 and aid the fat burning process.
Visit INNOSUPPS.COM | Link in bio

node.text:
Which body type are you? Read below ⤵️
I think I fit the Mesomorph type. 

Ectomorph: 
Lean and long, with difficulty building muscle

Endomorph: 
Big, high body fat, often pear-shaped, with a high tendency to store body fat

Mesomorph: 
Muscular and well-built, with a high metabolism and responsive muscle cells

Irrespective of whatever body type you have, we can all get fit! So wherever you’re starting from, just START and let consistency do it’s thing!

node.text:
I’ve never been keen on the term ‘chase your dreams,’ hear me out. My issue with it is that ‘dreams,’ which are normally so fantastical they seem highly unlikely, doesn’t sit well with me as the terminology one would use to describe a goal they actually believe they will achieve. 

If you see your goal as a dream, it remains fiction, almost as if you’re hoping for something to just happen, to be in with some luck. When you have a goal you need to claim it and own it from the start, it is not a wishful dream you are chasing, it is an endeavour you are pursuing with vigour until the end result is achieved. 

It’s no longer, ‘it could be me one day,’ it’s, ‘it will be me, I have a plan and it’s only a matter of time.’ 

Go be great today and everyday.
